<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1354,2017]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,330,1450,1474]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Description</emphasis>
. General shape of body typical of 
<taxonomicName box="[713,845,1450,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Libellulidae</taxonomicName>
, similar to known larvae of 
<taxonomicName authority="Costa et al." authorityName="Costa et al." box="[1149,1436,1450,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Libellulidae" genus="Macrothemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1149,1289,1450,1473]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Macrothemis</emphasis>
(Costa et al.)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,222,1482,1505]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[209,222,1482,1505]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
): Integument light brown, covered with small spiniform setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1354,2017]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Head. Large, general shape rectangular, almost twice as wide as long in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1224,1514,1537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[1211,1224,1514,1537]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Occipital margin concave (
<figureCitation box="[256,315,1546,1569]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig 
<number box="[302,315,1546,1569]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); eyes large and prominent in dorsal view; cephalic lobes rounded, not bulging, covered with minute spiniform setae. Antenna small, 
<number box="[496,508,1578,1601]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="7.0">7</number>
-segmented, with third antennomere longest (
<figureCitation box="[993,1059,1578,1601]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[1043,1059,1578,1601]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Labium small, triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1357,1421,1578,1601]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[1407,1421,1578,1601]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
), as wide as long, with 
<number box="[400,414,1610,1633]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="8.0">8</number>
lateral setae on each side of dorsal surface (
<number box="[921,935,1610,1633]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="5.0">5</number>
large, 
<number box="[1015,1029,1610,1633]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="3.0">3</number>
small); ligula not prominent, finely crenulated along margin; articulation of postmentum at level of anterior margin of mesocoxa. Labial palps triangular with 
<number box="[205,218,1674,1697]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="5.0">5</number>
setae (
<figureCitation box="[295,361,1674,1697]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[345,361,1674,1697]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); movable hook of moderate size, thick, pointed, as long as palpal setae; distal margin of palps with 
<number box="[151,178,1706,1729]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="10.0">10</number>
small crenulations, each bearing two to four smaller setae. Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[976,1082,1706,1729]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Figs. 5, 6</figureCitation>
) with following formula (
<emphasis box="[1375,1436,1706,1729]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Watson" box="[151,302,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="68" refString="Watson, M. C. (1956) The utilization of mandibular armature in taxonomic studies of anisopterous nymphs. Transactions" type="book" year="1956">
Watson, 
<number box="[244,302,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="1956.0">1956</number>
</bibRefCitation>
): L 
<number box="[343,356,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[363,376,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[383,396,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[403,416,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="4.0">4</number>
ab/ 
<number box="[462,475,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[482,495,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[502,515,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[522,535,1738,1761]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="4.0">4</number>
y abd.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1354,2017]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Thorax. Pronotum slightly quadrate. Prothoracic processes large with six teeth in posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1359,1770,1793]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[1343,1359,1770,1793]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wing pads parallel extending to distal end of S 
<number box="[614,630,1802,1825]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="6.0">6</number>
. Legs long, the hind leg surpassing distal margin of anal pyramid when extended to side of body, femora with a row of short stiff setae along dorsal margin and with one dark band near to the distal end (
<figureCitation box="[268,331,1866,1889]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[318,331,1866,1889]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1354,2017]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Abdomen. Ovoid, with dark mid-dorsal bands on S 
<number box="[750,764,1898,1921]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="3.0">3</number>
; small spines on lateral margin of S 
<number box="[1152,1165,1898,1921]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="8.0">8</number>
and 
<number box="[1218,1233,1898,1921]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="9.0">9</number>
, S 
<number box="[1260,1274,1898,1921]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="9.0">9</number>
curved inward (
<figureCitation box="[160,218,1930,1953]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[208,218,1930,1953]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hooks present on S 
<number box="[516,558,1930,1953]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="6.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="3.0">3–9</number>
, segment 
<number box="[665,678,1930,1953]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="3.0">3</number>
small; those on segments 
<number box="[957,998,1930,1953]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6–9</number>
well developed, highest on S 
<number box="[1311,1326,1930,1953]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="7.0">7</number>
, declining posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[281,347,1962,1985]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 11" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,197,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1901]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 11. Macrothemis heteronycha: (1) larva, dorsal view; (2) antenna; (3) labium; (4) labial palp; (5) left mandible; (6) right mandible; (7) prothoracic process; (8) abdomen, lateral view; (9) caudal appendages, dorsal view (10) Macrothemis inacuta, labial palp (after Novelo-Gutiérrez &amp; Ramirez, 1998), (11). Macrothemis pseudimitans, labial palp (after Limongi, 1989)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195946/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[332,347,1962,1985]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal appendages short (
